<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="85" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
Differs from other genera in 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" order="Polyporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" rank="order">Polyporales</taxonomicName>
by resupinate basidiocarps becoming rigid and light-weight upon drying, a monomitic hyphal system, thick-walled generative hyphae bearing both clamp connections and simple septa and hyaline, thin-walled, smooth, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="IKI–">IKI-</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="CB–">CB-</normalizedToken>
basidiospores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="85" type="type species">
